# {{PROJECT_NAME}}

FastAPI + DynamoDB app with CloudMock for local development.

## Getting Started

### 1. Start CloudMock

```bash
docker compose up
# or
npx cloudmock
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Run the API

```bash
uvicorn app:app --reload
```

API docs at http://localhost:8000/docs.

## API

| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /items | Create an item |
| GET | /items | List all items |
| GET | /items/{id} | Get an item |
| DELETE | /items/{id} | Delete an item |

Example:

```bash
curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/items \
  -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \
  -d '{"id":"1","name":"Widget","price":9.99}'
```

## Testing

```bash
pytest
```

Uses `cloudmock` fixture — no Docker required for tests.

## CloudMock DevTools

Open [http://localhost:4500](http://localhost:4500) to explore traces and topology.
